definition.value: A primary ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the amino group of 2-amino-2-deoxy-D-galactopyranose. Major species at pH 7.3.
An antigenic substance produced in tumour cells, which triggers an immune response in the host.
A hydroperoxy polyunsaturated fatty acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of (15S)-hydroperoxy-(11Z,13E)-icosadienoic acid. Major species at pH 7.3.
A non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid that is L-propargylglycine which is carrying a hydroxy group at the 3R position.
A nucleoside 5'-monophosphate(2-) that results from the removal of two protons from the phosphate group of N(6)-methyl-AMP.
A hydroperoxy fatty acid that is (11Z,13E)-icosadienoic acid in which the pro-S hydrogen at position 15 has been replaced by a hydroperoxy group.
A beta-D-glucoside resulting from the formal condensation of beta-D-glucoyranose with the alcoholic hydroxy group of 18-hydroxyocctadec-9-enoic acid.
A monounsaturated fatty acid that is (2E)-hexenoic acid in which the hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a methyl group. A malodourous component in the sweat of schizophrenics.
